HALIBURTON - OUR CANADIAN COUSINS
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    Should you bold 'village' dwellers every venture north of the A316
    into what the locals call the true St Margarets you may find
    yourself ambling along the long and gently curving avenue that is
    Haliburton Road. Following the path of the River Crane on its last
    tidal half mile before emptying into the Thames this little slice
    of Arcadia also marks the border between Hounslow and Richmond.

